# SvelteKit Frontend Patterns

- Keep Svelte components focused on presentation and user intent; call Tauri commands for native actions.
- Centralize app state in stores (profiles, thumbnails, groups, links, settings) with typed models matching backend payloads.
- Prefer event-driven updates (`listen`) over polling when backend emits thumbnail/profile/focus changes.
- Treat backend data as authoritative; avoid duplicating business logic in components.
- Use strict TypeScript types for command responses and event payloads.
- Keep UI interactions deterministic: optimistic updates only when rollback paths are implemented.
- Keep accessibility and keyboard navigation intact for all settings and management views.
